      "content": "It sounds like you are carrying a tremendous weight of despair, and it's completely understandable to feel overwhelmed by the weight of the world's problems. When everything feels so bleak, the small joys and future plans can feel utterly meaningless. Please remember that while the news highlights crises, it doesn't capture the resilience or the small pockets of good happening every day. Focusing on what you *can* control, even in tiny ways, can sometimes offer a small anchor when the big picture feels too terrifying.",
