      "content": "That feeling of futility is a very real and heavy one when facing such massive global uncertainty. It's a profoundly honest feeling, and you don't have to pretend to be okay if you aren't. Perhaps instead of trying to build a life that lasts forever, you can focus on making the *present* moment feel as solid and meaningful as possible, even if it's temporary. This isn't about denial; it's about finding a way to sustain yourself right now while the storm rages outside.",
      "source": "target",
